<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880217-0181 </DOCNO><HL> Datum Plans to Buy Austron </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DATM ATRN </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> ANAHEIM, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Datum Inc. said it signed a letter of intent to acquire Austron Inc. at $3.25 a share, or a total of $11.7 million.    Austron, based in Austin, Texas, has a total of 3,599,927 shares outstanding. Both companies make electronic instruments for military, industrial, space and commercial applications.    Completion of the acquisition is subject to a definitive agreement, approval by both boards, and regulatory approvals.    In the nine-month period ended Sept. 30, Datum earned $761,000, or 28 cents a share, on revenue of $20.7 million. In its fiscal year ended June 30, Austron earned $356,192, or 10 cents a share, on sales of $8 million. </TEXT></DOC>